                  For use of ros_matlab_bridge

------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------Pre-configuation------------------------------
step1:run MATLAB
step2:>>pathtool
step3:add /jsonlab/fsroot/json to the path(use add Folder), click save, if shows "cannot write the file", 
make sure to use "chmod 777" to give your user account writing permission


For ROS:
Be sure to open tcpic server  "rosrun rosbridge_server rosbridge_tcp.py"



--------------------------------Subscribe a topic------------------------------------
Set subs=true, 

The sample susbscribe Json message is "subscribe.json" 

you can change the topic you want to subscribe 

the output will be show on the screen if MATLAB recieves data (ans={})




--------------------------------advertise a topic and pulish info------------------------------------
Set ad_pub=true

The sample susbscribe Json message is "advertise.json" 

The sample susbscribe Json message is "publish.json" 

You can change the name of the topic you want to create by change the topic name in "advertise.json" 

If the topic is ALREADY exist, please comment the advertise and just use publish

You can change the name of the data and typy of data you want to publish in "publish.json" 
